<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=182&amp;p=1645#p1645"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />system or to the Famicom-to-NES converter<br /></div><br /><br />Both.<br /><br />For the Famicom-&gt;NES adapter...<br />Just solder pin 18 on the NES side of the connector to pin 46 of the Famicom side of the connector.<br /><br />For the NES,<br />Solder pin 18 of the NES cart connector to a series resistor 100K then a 1uF or higher non-polarized cap to pin 3 of the EXP connector on the bottom.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45">drk421</a> — Mon Mar 21, 2005 6:46 pm</p><hr />
